  "prompt": "Can I have a laptop bag apart from the 7kg bag (which is allowed for free) in the cabin space for jet airways?",
  "response": "As of the latest information available up to 2023, Jet Airways allows passengers to carry cabin baggage within specified limits. Typically, passengers are allowed one carry-on bag and may also be permitted to carry an additional personal item, such as a laptop bag, handbag, or small backpack.\n\nHowever, weight and size restrictions do apply:\n1. The main carry-on bag should generally not exceed a weight limit of 7 kg.\n2. The laptop bag or personal item should be small enough to fit under the seat in front of you.\n\nIt's always recommended to check the latest baggage policies directly on Jet Airways' website or contact their customer service, as airline policies can be subject to change.",
